X_{1},\dots,X_{n}
\theta
\lambda
-\infty<\theta<\infty
0<\lambda<\infty
X-\theta
 p(x|\theta,\lambda)=\lambda\exp[-\lambda(x-\theta)],\ \theta\leq x<\infty, 
E(X-\theta)=E(X)-E(\theta)=E(X)-\theta
E(X-\theta)=1/\lambda
Var(X-\theta)=Var(X)+Var(\theta)=Var(X)
E(X^{2})=\theta^{2}+2\theta/\lambda+2/\lambda^{2}
 Var(X)=\left(\theta^{2}+\frac{2\theta}{\lambda}+\frac{2}{\lambda^{2}}\right)-\left(\theta+\frac{1}{\lambda}\right)^{2}.
